# Twingate relay GCP IPs — libsdwan resolves these via its own DoH and
# connects by IP, so the twingate.com domain entry doesn't help.
# Relay endpoints are returned by the controller API after login (not in DNS),
# so /16 aggregates are the only way to cover their rotation across
# europe-west*, asia-east*, us-*. Control-plane and STUN IPs are auto-
# resolved at build time from scripts/dynamic-hosts.txt — no need to list
# their /16s here.
34.6.0.0/16
34.13.0.0/16
34.39.0.0/16
34.65.0.0/16
34.89.0.0/16
34.107.0.0/16
34.158.0.0/16
34.159.0.0/16
